Key Match Events: Daulton Varsho and Spencer Horwitz each hit two-run homers in the first inning.
José Berríos tossed six shutout innings.
Toronto hit three two-run homers, including two in a seven-run first inning.
The Blue Jays routed the Minnesota Twins 15-0.
W. Wagner hit a ground rule double and a home run.
L. Jimenez singled to center, scoring two runs.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was held at Target Field in Minneapolis, Minnesota.
The game lasted 2 hours and 30 minutes.
Umpires for the game were Derek Thomas, Nic Lentz, Will Little, and Lance Barksdale.
